{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> δεσπότ-ης</b>, ου, ; <br /> <i>vocative</i> δέσποτᾰ: <i>Ionic dialect</i> <i>accusative</i> δεσπότεα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.91, +others, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Syr.D.” 25 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>master, lord,</b> properly <b>the master of the house,</b> δόμων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 60, etc.; ὄμμα γὰρ δόμων νομίζω δεσπότου παρουσίαν [prev. author] “Pers.” 169 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>plural</i>, of a family, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ag.” 32, “Ch.” 53, 82 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs</a>]; in respect of slaves, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Parmenides” 133d; δοῦλοι καὶ δ. οὐκ ἄν ποτε γένοιντο φίλοι [prev. author] “Lg.” 757a, etc.; δ. καὶ δοῦλος 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1253b6, compare 1278b35; ὦ δέσποτ᾽ ἄναξ 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 90 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὦναξ δέσποτα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 389, “fragment” 598; δέσποτ᾽ ἄναξ 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 312.5. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>despot, absolute ruler,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.89, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.77; τύραννος καὶ δ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 859a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the Roman <b>Emperors,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 2.568, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 55.12, 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus 1.6.4; γᾶς καὶ θαλάσσας δ. “IG” 12(2).216 (from Mytilene). \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> of the gods, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 535, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 88, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 875, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.2.13. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>dominant planet,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Vett. Val. 5.16. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> generally, <b>master, lord, owner,</b> κώμου, ναῶν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 6.18, “P.” 4.207; μαντευμάτων 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 27; τῶν Ἡρακλείων ὅπλων 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 262 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἑπτὰ δεσποτῶν, of the seven [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Chiefs” against Thebes, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 636; τοῦ ὄρτυγος 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 9.108.—Not in 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus (for metrical reasons), though he uses δέσποινα in 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” (Prob. for δεμσποτ- 'lord of the house', compare δόμος.) \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1203","accentedUnicode":"δεσπότης","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3617","matchingForm":"οἰκοδεσπότης","stepTransliteration":"oikodespotēs","gloss":"householder","_zh_tw_Gloss":"家主","_es_Gloss":"dueño de casa","_zh_Gloss":"家主"}],"shortDef":"master; Sovereign Lord","mediumDef":"master; Sovereign Lord <br /><b>a lord, master,</b> especially of slaves, <ref='1Ti.6.1'>1Tim. 6:1</ref>, 2; <ref='2Ti.2.21'>2Tim. 2:21;</ref> <ref='Tit.2.9'>Tit. 2:9;</ref> <ref='1Pe.2.18'>1Pet. 2:18;</ref> by impl. as denoting the possession of supreme authority, <b>Lord, sovereign,</b> used of God, <ref='Luk.2.29'>Lk. 2:29</ref>; <ref='Act.4.24'>Acts 4:24;</ref> <ref='Rev.6.10'>Rev. 6:10;</ref> and of Christ, <ref='2Pe.2.1'>2Pet. 2:1;</ref> Jude 4","stepGloss":"master","stepTransliteration":"despotēs","count":10,"_es_Definition":"Señor, Maestro (con ref. a Dios y a Cristo) ; dueño o propietario de esclavos, amo (de una casa)","_zh_tw_Definition":"主人, 主宰","_zh_Definition":"主人, 主宰","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"chúa; chúa chủ","_zh_tw_Gloss":"主人","_es_Gloss":"amo ","_zh_Glo